This method name looks ambiguous to me. I'm thinking it can be interpreted as two different meanings
* Test for previously failed option (now succeeded)
* Test for options that have failed (now failing)

In this issue, "previously failed" is correct but it doesn't mean anything. This is because generally regression tests are for fixing "previously failed" something. Would you make the name more straightforward? (ex. testOfflineImageViewerMaxSizeAndStepOptions)
